      <description>&lt;p&gt;A curated 
&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.notion.so/02cb1499079b47acb7e719fe7b08b6fa?v=f2e66d86cdd24e0a892f81b5b8130a6c&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;list&lt;/a&gt; of early-career science journalism jobs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An advice thread: &lt;blockquote class=&#34;twitter-tweet&#34;&gt;&lt;p lang=&#34;en&#34; dir=&#34;ltr&#34;&gt;🧵 with unsolicited job advice for new PhDs and almost-done postdocs: &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;If you enjoy scientific writing, consider looking into freelance scientific editing/writing. The Council of Science Editors (CSE) is a great place to start. Their job board is hopping right now. (+)&lt;/p&gt;&amp;mdash; Kate Kadash-Edmondson (@KadashKate) &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/KadashKate/status/1253763391560265728?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&#34;&gt;April 24, 2020&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;script async src=&#34;https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js&#34; charset=&#34;utf-8&#34;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Another jobs account: &lt;blockquote class=&#34;twitter-tweet&#34;&gt;&lt;p lang=&#34;en&#34; dir=&#34;ltr&#34;&gt;Thinking of a career outside of academia? Follow our companion account, &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/aslo_opps?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&#34;&gt;@aslo_opps&lt;/a&gt;! We share jobs and opportunities in &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/hashtag/SciencePolicy?src=hash&amp;amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&#34;&gt;#SciencePolicy&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/hashtag/SciComm?src=hash&amp;amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&#34;&gt;#SciComm&lt;/a&gt;, &amp;amp; more. Whether you’re actively looking for a job, or want to get a sense of what’s out there, &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/aslo_opps?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&#34;&gt;@aslo_opps&lt;/a&gt; is a great resource. &lt;a href=&#34;https://t.co/hI2eJS6xf7&#34;&gt;pic.twitter.com/hI2eJS6xf7&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;mdash; ASLO (@aslo_org) &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/aslo_org/status/1263477146921562112?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&#34;&gt;May 21, 2020&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;script async src=&#34;https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js&#34; charset=&#34;utf-8&#34;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
